It is a simple Angular JS Application, packaged with Grunt.

AngularJS: [1.6.9] | jQuery: [3.3.1] | Grunt: [1.0.2] | npm: [5.8.0]

Steps:
-----
1- Install node.js
2- Install grunt cli: npm install -g grunt-cli
3- Create package.json : npm init
4- In package.json add "start" inside "scripts" object: "start" : "http-server -a <IP/Address> -p <portNumber>"
5- to add dependencies in package.json: npm install <module> 	--save-dev
					npm install grunt	--save-dev
					npm install grunt-contrib-jshint 	--save-dev
					npm install grunt-contrib-nodeunit 	--save-dev
					npm install grunt-contrib-uglify 	--save-dev
6- Now to create Gruntfile.js: simply create it manually in root folder i.e. alongside package.json file.

To Run:
------
Just go to app/ from shell/cmd/git bash and type 'npm start'
